overview.longBusinessSummary: Summit Midstream Corporation focuses on owning, developing, and operating midstream energy infrastructure assets primarily shale formations in the continental United States. The company operates through Rockies, Permian, Piceance, Mid-Con, and Northeast segments. It owns, develops, and operates natural gas, crude oil, produced water gathering systems, and transmission pipelines. The company serves natural gas and crude oil producers. Summit Midstream Corporation was founded in 2009 and is based in Houston, Texas.
